        // solving the linear DP problem, and then solving it again by forcing index 0 to be a peak,
        // and taking the minimum of the two results.

        // DP function for linear array (indices 0 to n-1, subject to adjacency constraints)
        // dp[i][j] = minimum cost to select exactly j non-adjacent peaks from indices 0..i.
        // Since we need AT LEAST k peaks, we need to track up to k.

